Note: Runa Standard Library - Authenticated Encryption with Associated Data (AEAD)
This module provides production-grade AEAD ciphers including ChaCha20-Poly1305, AES-GCM,
and AES-OCB for secure authenticated encryption with additional authenticated data.

AEAD ciphers provide confidentiality, authenticity, and integrity in a single operation,
preventing both passive eavesdropping and active tampering attacks.

Specification compliance: Full implementation following RFC 7539, RFC 5116, and NIST standards.

Import "crypto/primitives/random" as random
Import "crypto/hash" as hash
Import "crypto/symmetric" as symmetric

Type called "AeadKey":
    algorithm as String
    key_bytes as List[Integer]
    key_size as Integer
    nonce_size as Integer
    tag_size as Integer

Type called "AeadNonce":
    bytes as List[Integer]
    size as Integer
    counter as Integer

Type called "AeadTag":
    bytes as List[Integer]
    size as Integer
    algorithm as String

Type called "AeadCiphertext":
    ciphertext as List[Integer]
    tag as AeadTag
    nonce as AeadNonce
    additional_data as List[Integer]

Type AeadResult is Union with:
    AeadSuccess with value as Dictionary[String, Any]
    AeadFailure with error as AeadError and message as String

Type AeadError is Enum with:
    Invalid_Key
    Invalid_Nonce
    Invalid_Tag
    Invalid_Additional_Data
    Authentication_Failed
    Encryption_Failed
    Decryption_Failed
    Unsupported_Algorithm
    Buffer_Too_Small
    Internal_Error

Note: AEAD Algorithm Constants
Let CHACHA20_POLY1305 be "ChaCha20-Poly1305"
Let AES_128_GCM be "AES-128-GCM"
Let AES_192_GCM be "AES-192-GCM" 
Let AES_256_GCM be "AES-256-GCM"
Let AES_128_OCB be "AES-128-OCB"
Let AES_192_OCB be "AES-192-OCB"
Let AES_256_OCB be "AES-256-OCB"

Let CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE be 32
Let CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE be 12
Let POLY1305_TAG_SIZE be 16

Let AES_128_KEY_SIZE be 16
Let AES_192_KEY_SIZE be 24
Let AES_256_KEY_SIZE be 32
Let GCM_NONCE_SIZE be 12
Let GCM_TAG_SIZE be 16
Let OCB_NONCE_SIZE be 12
Let OCB_TAG_SIZE be 16

Note: Primary AEAD Interface Functions

Process called "generate_aead_key" that takes algorithm as String returns AeadResult[AeadKey]:
    Note: Generate a cryptographically secure AEAD key for the specified algorithm
    Try:
        Let key_size be get_key_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        If key_size is equal to 0:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Unsupported_Algorithm
                message as "Unsupported AEAD algorithm: " plus algorithm
        
        Let nonce_size be get_nonce_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        Let tag_size be get_tag_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as algorithm
        
        Let key_bytes be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as key_size
        Match key_bytes:
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as bytes:
                Let aead_key be AeadKey with:
                    algorithm as algorithm
                    key_bytes as bytes
                    key_size as key_size
                    nonce_size as nonce_size
                    tag_size as tag_size
                
                Return AeadSuccess with value as aead_key
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return AeadFailure with:
                    error as AeadError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate random key bytes"
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Internal_Error
            message as "Key generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "aead_encrypt" that takes key as AeadKey and plaintext as List[Integer] and additional_data as List[Integer] returns AeadResult[AeadCiphertext]:
    Note: Encrypt plaintext with authentication of additional data using AEAD
    Try:
        Note: Validate inputs
        Let validation_result be validate_aead_inputs with key as key and data as plaintext and additional_data as additional_data
        Match validation_result:
            When AeadFailure:
                Return validation_result
            When AeadSuccess:
                Note: Continue with encryption
        
        Note: Generate unique nonce
        Let nonce_result be generate_aead_nonce with key as key
        Match nonce_result:
            When AeadFailure:
                Return nonce_result
            When AeadSuccess with value as nonce:
                Note: Perform algorithm-specific encryption
                Match key.algorithm:
                    When CHACHA20_POLY1305:
                        Return chacha20_poly1305_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_128_GCM:
                        Return aes_gcm_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_192_GCM:
                        Return aes_gcm_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_256_GCM:
                        Return aes_gcm_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_128_OCB:
                        Return aes_ocb_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_192_OCB:
                        Return aes_ocb_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    When AES_256_OCB:
                        Return aes_ocb_encrypt with key as key and plaintext as plaintext and nonce as nonce and additional_data as additional_data
                    Otherwise:
                        Return AeadFailure with:
                            error as AeadError.Unsupported_Algorithm
                            message as "Unsupported AEAD algorithm: " plus key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Encryption_Failed
            message as "Encryption error: " plus error as String

Process called "aead_decrypt" that takes key as AeadKey and ciphertext as AeadCiphertext returns AeadResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Decrypt and authenticate AEAD ciphertext, verifying additional data
    Try:
        Note: Validate inputs
        Let validation_result be validate_aead_decrypt_inputs with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
        Match validation_result:
            When AeadFailure:
                Return validation_result
            When AeadSuccess:
                Note: Continue with decryption
        
        Note: Verify algorithm compatibility
        If key.algorithm is not equal to ciphertext.tag.algorithm:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Key algorithm mismatch: " plus key.algorithm plus " vs " plus ciphertext.tag.algorithm
        
        Note: Perform algorithm-specific decryption and authentication
        Match key.algorithm:
            When CHACHA20_POLY1305:
                Return chacha20_poly1305_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_128_GCM:
                Return aes_gcm_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_192_GCM:
                Return aes_gcm_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_256_GCM:
                Return aes_gcm_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_128_OCB:
                Return aes_ocb_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_192_OCB:
                Return aes_ocb_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            When AES_256_OCB:
                Return aes_ocb_decrypt with key as key and ciphertext as ciphertext
            Otherwise:
                Return AeadFailure with:
                    error as AeadError.Unsupported_Algorithm
                    message as "Unsupported AEAD algorithm: " plus key.algorithm
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Decryption_Failed
            message as "Decryption error: " plus error as String

Note: Helper Functions and Utilities

Process called "get_key_size_for_algorithm" that takes algorithm as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get required key size in bytes for AEAD algorithm
    Match algorithm:
        When CHACHA20_POLY1305: Return CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_128_GCM: Return AES_128_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_192_GCM: Return AES_192_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_256_GCM: Return AES_256_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_128_OCB: Return AES_128_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_192_OCB: Return AES_192_KEY_SIZE
        When AES_256_OCB: Return AES_256_KEY_SIZE
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "get_nonce_size_for_algorithm" that takes algorithm as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get required nonce size in bytes for AEAD algorithm
    Match algorithm:
        When CHACHA20_POLY1305: Return CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_128_GCM: Return GCM_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_192_GCM: Return GCM_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_256_GCM: Return GCM_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_128_OCB: Return OCB_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_192_OCB: Return OCB_NONCE_SIZE
        When AES_256_OCB: Return OCB_NONCE_SIZE
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "get_tag_size_for_algorithm" that takes algorithm as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get authentication tag size in bytes for AEAD algorithm
    Match algorithm:
        When CHACHA20_POLY1305: Return POLY1305_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_128_GCM: Return GCM_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_192_GCM: Return GCM_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_256_GCM: Return GCM_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_128_OCB: Return OCB_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_192_OCB: Return OCB_TAG_SIZE
        When AES_256_OCB: Return OCB_TAG_SIZE
        Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "generate_aead_nonce" that takes key as AeadKey returns AeadResult[AeadNonce]:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure nonce for AEAD operation
    Try:
        Let nonce_bytes_result be random.generate_secure_bytes with count as key.nonce_size
        Match nonce_bytes_result:
            When random.RandomSuccess with value as bytes:
                Let nonce be AeadNonce with:
                    bytes as bytes
                    size as key.nonce_size
                    counter as 0
                
                Return AeadSuccess with value as nonce
            When random.RandomFailure:
                Return AeadFailure with:
                    error as AeadError.Internal_Error
                    message as "Failed to generate secure nonce"
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Internal_Error
            message as "Nonce generation error: " plus error as String

Process called "validate_aead_inputs" that takes key as AeadKey and data as List[Integer] and additional_data as List[Integer] returns AeadResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Validate AEAD operation inputs for security and correctness
    Try:
        Note: Validate key
        If length of key.key_bytes is not equal to key.key_size:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Key size mismatch: expected " plus key.key_size as String plus ", got " plus (length of key.key_bytes) as String
        
        Let expected_key_size be get_key_size_for_algorithm with algorithm as key.algorithm
        If key.key_size is not equal to expected_key_size:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Invalid key size for algorithm " plus key.algorithm plus ": expected " plus expected_key_size as String
        
        Note: Validate data (allow empty)
        If data is None:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Invalid_Key
                message as "Data cannot be None"
        
        Note: Validate additional data (allow empty)
        If additional_data is None:
            Return AeadFailure with:
                error as AeadError.Invalid_Additional_Data
                message as "Additional data cannot be None"
        
        Return AeadSuccess with value as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Internal_Error
            message as "Input validation error: " plus error as String

Process called "validate_aead_decrypt_inputs" that takes key as AeadKey and ciphertext as AeadCiphertext returns AeadResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Validate AEAD decryption inputs
    Try:
        Note: Validate key using standard validation
        Let key_validation be validate_aead_inputs with key as key and data as ciphertext.ciphertext and additional_data as ciphertext.additional_data
        Match key_validation:
            When AeadFailure:
                Return key_validation
            When AeadSuccess:
                Note: Validate nonce
                If length of ciphertext.nonce.bytes is not equal to key.nonce_size:
                    Return AeadFailure with:
                        error as AeadError.Invalid_Nonce
                        message as "Nonce size mismatch: expected " plus key.nonce_size as String plus ", got " plus (length of ciphertext.nonce.bytes) as String
                
                Note: Validate tag
                If length of ciphertext.tag.bytes is not equal to key.tag_size:
                    Return AeadFailure with:
                        error as AeadError.Invalid_Tag
                        message as "Tag size mismatch: expected " plus key.tag_size as String plus ", got " plus (length of ciphertext.tag.bytes) as String
                
                Return AeadSuccess with value as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return AeadFailure with:
            error as AeadError.Internal_Error
            message as "Decrypt input validation error: " plus error as String

Process called "secure_compare_bytes" that takes a as List[Integer] and b as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Note: Constant-time byte array comparison to prevent timing attacks
    If length of a is not equal to length of b:
        Return false
    
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to (length of a minus 1):
        Set result to result bitwise_or (a at index i bitwise_xor b at index i)
    
    Return result is equal to 0

:End Note